subsection.p:
(128)
Agreement patterns arising with quantifiers:
a. plural agreement in the case of [+count] nouns in the complement of cardinals and vague numerals (three books, many books, some books);
b. singular agreement in the case of [+count] nouns in the complement of the cardinal one (one book), the vague numeral some (some book), and distributive quantifiers (each book);
c. singular agreement with all [−count] nouns (some wine).
